{{Speciesbox | name = ''Tarentola darwini'' | image = | image_caption = | status = LC | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = | taxon = Tarentola darwini | authority = [[Hans Joger|Joger]] (1984) | synonyms = | synonyms_ref =<ref name="RDB"/> }} '''''Tarentola darwini''''' (English name: '''Darwin's wall gecko''') is a [[species]] of [[gecko]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Phyllodactylidae]]. The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Cape Verde]] Islands and are founded in the island of São Nicolau.<ref name="RDB">{{NRDB species|genus=Tarentola |species=darwini|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref>
The species is endemic to the islands of [[São Nicolau, Cape Verde|São Nicolau]], [[Sal, Cape Verde|Sal]], [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]] and [[Fogo, Cape Verde|Fogo]].<ref name="RDB"/>
==Etymology== The [[specific name (zoology)|specific name]] is named after [[Charles Darwin]] who visited the [[Santiago, Cape Verde|island of Santiago]] at Praia in 1832 .<ref name="RDB"/> It was named by [[Hans Joger]], more than a century after his visit in 1984.
