[[File:Дикий сад кіммерійці.png|thumb|Reconstruction of the site]]
The '''Dykyi Sad archaeological site''' constitutes the remains of an ancient port city discovered in the Dykyi Sad park ({{Lang-uk|Дикий Сад|lit=Wild Garden}}) in [[Mykolaiv, Ukraine]]. The site is dated to the [[Bilozerska culture]], around 1250–925 BC.<ref name="Gorbenko">{{cite journal|last2=Grebennikov|first2=Yuriy|date=2009|title=The 'Dykyi Sad' fortified settlement as a uniting link in the context of economic, political and cultural relation of 1200-1000 BC (the Baltic Shore, the Pontic region and the Mediterranean)|url=https://repozytorium.amu.edu.pl/bitstream/10593/13272/1/BPS-14-18_K_V_Gorbenko%20Y_S_Grebennikov%20THE%20%E2%80%98DYKYI%20SAD%E2%80%99%20FORTIFIED%20SETTLEMENT%20AS%20A%20UNITING%20LINK%20IN%20THE%20CONTEXT%20OF%20ECONOMIC%2c%20POLITICAL%20AND%20CULTURAL%20RELATION%20OF%201200-1000%20BC%20PP_375-390.pdf|journal=Baltic-Pontic Studies|volume=14|pages=375–390|issn=1231-0344|last1=Gorbenko|first1=Kirill|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Горбенко|first=К.В.|date=2014|title=Городище "Дикий Сад" в контексте социально-экономических и культурных связей балтийского и черноморского регионов XІII–XI вв. до н.э.|url=http://repo.gsu.by/xmlui/handle/123456789/1626|journal=Известия Гомельского государственного университета имени Ф. Скорины|volume=Nº 4|issue=85|doi=|pmid=|access-date=|via=}}</ref>

Researchers have proposed that the site is the "City of the [[Cimmerians]]" mentioned by [[Homer]] in the [[Odyssey]].<ref>Odyssey xi.12.</ref> Though the [[geography of the Odyssey]] is a contentious field, if true, this would make Mykolaiv the oldest city in Ukraine that is mentioned in written sources.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ua-travel.info/ua/news_details/0/37.html|title=Миколаїв невдовзі буде визнано найстарішим містом України|website=ua-travel.info|access-date=2016-09-13}}</ref>

