{{use dmy dates|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox film | name = Eyes of a Thief | image = Eyes of a Thief.jpg | caption = Film poster | director = [[Najwa Najjar]] | producer = | writer = Najwa Najjar | starring = [[Khaled Abol Naga]] | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2014|9|27|Brazil|2014|10|1|Palestine|df=yes}} | runtime = 98 minutes | country = Palestine | language = Arabic | budget = }}
'''''Eyes of a Thief''''' ({{lang-ar|عيون الحرامية}}) is a 2014 Palestinian [[drama film]] directed by [[Najwa Najjar]]. It is Najjar's second feature film, and is based in part on [[Wadi al-Haramiya sniper attack|an incident]] that took place in [[Silwad]] in 2002. It was selected as the [[List of Palestinian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Palestinian entry]] for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[87th Academy Awards]], but was not nominated.<ref name="Palestine">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-palestine-selects-eyes-a-735662 |title=Oscars: Palestine Selects ‘Eyes of a Thief’ for Foreign-Language Category |accessdate=25 September 2014 |work=Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> The film is set in the [[West Bank]]. Its world premiere took place at the Ramallah Cultural Palace in [[Ramallah, Palestine]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ritman|first1=Alex|title=Oscars: Palestine Selects ‘Eyes of a Thief’ for Foreign-Language Category|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-palestine-selects-eyes-a-735662|accessdate=22 October 2014|date=25 September 2014}}</ref>
==Cast== * [[Khaled Abol Naga]] as Tarek Khedr * [[Souad Massi]] as Lila * [[Nisreen Faour]] as Duniya * [[Maisa Abd Elhadi]] as Houda (as Maisa Abdel Hadi) * [[Areen Omari]] as Salwa
==See also== * [[List of submissions to the 87th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]] * [[List of Palestinian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]
