{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Doruma–Dungu |latin = Dioecesis Dorumaensis-Dunguensis |country = {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kisangani|Kisangani]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 44,000 |population = 200,000 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 105,000 |catholics_percent= 52.5 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Richard Domba Mady]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Doruma–Dungu''' ({{lang-la|Dorumaën(sis) – Dunguen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Doruma]]–[[Dungu, Democratic Republic of the Congo|Dungu]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kisangani|Kisangani]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
==History== * February 24, 1958: Established as Apostolic Prefecture of Doruma from the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Niangara]] * September 26, 1967: Promoted as Diocese of Doruma * July 3, 1970: Renamed as Diocese of Doruma – Dungu
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Doruma–Dungu ([[Latin Rite]]) ** Bishop Richard Domba Mady (since 1994.03.14) ** Bishop [[Emile Aiti Waro Leru’a]] (1983.05.07 – 1989.09.25) ** Bishop [[Guillaume van den Elzen]], [[Augustinians|O.S.A.]] (1970.07.03 – 1983.05.07) * Bishops of Doruma (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Guillaume van den Elzen, O.S.A. (1967.09.26 – 1970.07.03) * Prefects Apostolic of Doruma (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Guillaume van den Elzen, O.S.A. (1958.11.13 – 1967.09.26)
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in the Democratic Republic of the Congo]]
==Sources== * [http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/doru0.htm GCatholic.org] * [http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/ddoru.html Catholic Hierarchy]
