{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} {{Infobox Protected area | name = Royal Jozini Big 6 | iucn_category = | map = Swaziland | relief = 1 | map_caption = Location in Swaziland | location = [[Shiselweni]], {{flag|Swaziland}} | nearest_town = [[Lavumisa]], [[Swaziland]] | coordinates = {{coord|27|16|50.60|S|31|57|18.39|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = 160km<sup>2</sup> | established = 2008 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }}
The '''Royal Jozini''' Big 6 Private Estate is a private game reserve, currently under development. It is located in the foothills of the [[Lebombo Mountains|Lubombo Mountains]] and includes the northern part of Lake Jozini in [[Swaziland]]. It is part of the Nsubane-Pongola Transfrontier Conservation and Resource Area<ref>http://www.noboundaries.co.za/pongola-1.htm</ref> established by a Swaziland/South Africa Protocol and will be known as "Lake Jozini Transfrontier Park"<ref>http://www.peaceparks.org/news.php?pid=162&mid=729</ref> covering some 40 000 hectares in total. When the reserve is completed in 2010,<ref>http://www.royaljozini.net/site/awdep.asp?depnum=28334{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> it will contain the [[Big Five game|Big Five]], as well as [[Tigerfish|tiger fish]], thus the term 'Big 6'. The Estate will also include a number of private lodges, a waterfront area including a boating marina, jetty and slipway, a casino, hotel and 18 hole golf course designed by [[Hugh Baiocchi]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.royaljozini.net/site/awdep.asp?depnum=28332 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-11-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303194950/http://www.royaljozini.net/site/awdep.asp?depnum=28332 |archivedate=2016-03-03 |df= }}</ref>
