{{Multiple issues|{{Notability|Biographies|date=January 2015}} {{No footnotes|date=January 2015}} }} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Simone | background = solo_singer | image = <!-- must be an image hosted on en.wikipedia or in Wikimedia Commons --> | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Simone Philip Kamel | birth_date = June 14 | birth_place = [[Shubra (administrative region)|Shubra]], [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]] | origin = | genre =[[Pop music|Pop]] | occupation = {{flatlist| * Singer * Actress }} | years_active = 1987–present | label = | associated_acts =[[Hamid Al-Shairi]], [[Amr Diab]] }}
'''Simone Philip Kamel''' ({{lang-arz|سيمون فيليپ كامل}}), mononymously known as '''Simone''', born June 14, is an Egyptian singer, that throughout the 1990s was famous for her soprano voice. Her most famous songs include "{{lang|ar|مش نظرة وابتسامة}}" (''Not Just a Look and a Smile''), "{{lang|ar|تاكسي}}" (''Taxi''), "{{lang|ar|خاف مني}}" (''Fear Me''), "{{lang|ar|مبسوطة}}" (''Happy''), "{{lang|ar|تاني تاني}}" (''Again, Again''), "{{lang|ar|ميرسي}}" (''Thank You''), "{{lang|ar|ساعتى مش مظبوطة}}" (''My Watch is not Set''), "{{lang|ar|كازانوفا}}" (''Casanova''), "{{lang|ar|بتكلم جد}}" (''I'm Talking Seriously''). She also released a Greek/Arabic song called ''Munawar'' for the Greek-Egyptian Friendship Festival.
== Life and career ==
=== Early life and education === Simone has a bachelor's degree in [[French literature]] from the [[American University in Cairo]].
=== Beginning of musical career === She participated in the Greek-Egyptian Friendship Festival where she sang a song in Greek.
